components.readme:
# ion-slide

The Slide component is a child component of [Slides](../Slides). The template
should be written as `ion-slide`. Any slide content should be written
in this component and it should be used in conjunction with [Slides](../Slides).

See the [Slides API Docs](../Slides) for more usage information.

# stellar-slides

The Slides component is a multi-section container. Each section can be swiped
or dragged between. It contains any number of [Slide](../Slide) components.


Adopted from Swiper.js:
The most modern mobile touch slider and framework with hardware accelerated transitions.

http://www.idangero.us/swiper/

Copyright 2016, Vladimir Kharlampidi
The iDangero.us
http://www.idangero.us/

Licensed under MIT

methods.docs: Get the index of the previous slide.

methods.docs: Get whether or not the current slide is the first slide.

methods.name: isEnd
methods.docs: Get whether or not the current slide is the last slide.

methods.name: length
methods.docs: Get the total number of slides.

methods.name: lockSwipes
methods.docs: Lock or unlock the ability to slide to change slides.

methods.name: lockSwipeToNext
methods.docs: Lock or unlock the ability to slide to the next slides.

methods.name: lockSwipeToPrev
methods.docs: Lock or unlock the ability to slide to the previous slides.

methods.name: update
methods.docs:
Update the underlying slider implementation. Call this if you've added or removed
child slides.
